{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899629023,"sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdc2e7d001o2JSSTHNIhxThr","messageID":"msg_d7bdc1f53001LPUCW5T65oyOWY","sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_931bc07abc7b41198f6971e6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (top-level directories and key files)\n2. Any existing spec files (look for *.md files in docs/, specs/, or similar directories, especially any delta-spec.md or spec.md files)\n3. Any existing OpenSpec format examples in the project\n4. The current state of documentation (docs/ directory if it exists)\n5. Any existing architecture design documents or API documentation\n\nReturn:\n- Project structure overview\n- Paths to any existing spec files and their format/pattern\n- Current state of docs/ directory\n- Any relevant patterns for writing specs in this project","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28423ba8dffeBpK4Uf1InNkHHT (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a thorough understanding of the project. Here is the complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\nThe project is a **Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents** (Go + Python monorepo). Here are the top-level directories and key files:\n\n**Top-level directories:**\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `pkg/` | Go packages (core server logic) |\n| `cmd/` | Go binaries (entrypoints) |\n| `client-go/` | Generated Kubernetes client code |\n| `python-sdk/` / `sdk-python/` | Python SDK |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | Python CLI toolkit |\n| `code-execution/` | PicoD code execution daemon (Go) |\n| `session-routing/` | Router / session-aware proxy (Go) |\n| `session-store/` | Redis/Valkey session store (Go) |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Sandbox orchestration logic |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment specs, Helm charts |\n| `manifests/` | Kubernetes CRD YAML definitions |\n| `docker/` | Docker build files |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD pipeline configuration |\n| `integrations/` | Third-party integrations (Dify plugin) |\n| `example/` | Example applications (pcap_analyzer) |\n| `changes/` | **Change request directories (AR-001 through AR-043)** |\n| `docs/` | Docusaurus 3.x documentation site |\n| `test/` / `testing/` | Test files and TDD manifest |\n| `hack/` | Code generation scripts |\n| `agentd/` | Idle cleanup controller |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Idle cleanup spec/design |\n\n**Key root-level files:**\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `project.md` | OpenSpec project context (purpose, tech stack, architecture, conventions) |\n| `design.md` | AR-040: Python SDK unit test design document |\n| `delta-spec.md` | AR-038: Go unit test delta spec (workloadmanager) |\n| `proposal.md` | AR-043: Architecture design & API documentation proposal |\n| `tasks.md` | AR-023: CLI invoke/status command task breakdown |\n| `test_spec.md` | TDD specification with test case naming conventions |\n| `.sdd_prompt.md` | SDD (Software Design Document) prompt template |\n| `Makefile` | Build targets |\n| `go.mod` / `go.sum` | Go module definition |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Existing Spec Files and Their Formats\n\nThe project uses a **multi-tier spec system** with three distinct spec file types:\n\n#### A. Feature-level `spec.md` files (component specifications)\n\nLocated in feature directories, these define the complete specification for a component:\n\n| Path | Topic |\n|------|-------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../code-execution/spec.md` | PicoD code execution daemon |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../session-routing/spec.md` | Session routing / proxy |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../session-store/spec.md` | Session store |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../cli-toolkit/spec.md` | CLI toolkit |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../deployment/spec.md` | Deployment |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../python-sdk/spec.md` | Python SDK |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../idle-cleanup/spec.md` | Idle cleanup |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../ci-cd/spec.md` | CI/CD |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../integrations/spec.md` | Integrations |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` | Sandbox orchestration |\n\n**Format pattern for `spec.md`:**\n```markdown\n# <Component Name> Specification\n\n## Purpose\n<One-paragraph description>\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: <Requirement Name>\nThe system SHALL <behavior description>.\n\n#### Scenario: <Scenario Name>\n- **GIVEN** <preconditions>\n- **WHEN** <action>\n- **THEN** <expected outcomes>\n```\n\nKey conventions:\n- Uses **RFC 2119 normative language**: SHALL (mandatory), SHOULD (recommended), MAY (optional)\n- Each requirement has one or more **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios** (BDD style)\n- Requirements are grouped by functional area\n\n#### B. Change-level `delta-spec.md` files (incremental specs)\n\nLocated in `changes/AR-XXX/` directories, these define the spec for a specific change request:\n\n| Path Pattern | Example |\n|-------------|---------|\n| `changes/AR-XXX/delta-spec.md` | 43 change requests (AR-001 through AR-043) |\n| Root-level `delta-spec.md` | AR-038: Go unit tests for workloadmanager |\n\n**Format pattern for mature delta-spec.md (e.g., AR-036, AR-038):**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX: <Title> -- Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n- **Module:** <module path>\n- **Language:** <language>\n- **Size:** <S/M/L>\n- **Base specs:** <paths to spec.md files this builds on>\n\n## Scope\n<Description of what this delta spec covers>\n\n---\n\n## R-1: <Requirement Group Name>\n**Scope:** <files/functions covered>\n\n### Requirement: <Specific Requirement>\n\n#### Scenario: <Scenario Name>\n- **GIVEN** <preconditions>\n- **WHEN** <action>\n- **THEN** <expected outcomes>\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `path/to/file.go` | **NEW** -- description |\n\n## Dependencies\n- `package/name` -- description (已有/existing)\n\n## Status\n- [ ] Spec review\n- [ ] Implementation\n- [ ] Verification\n```\n\n**Format pattern for skeleton delta-spec.md (e.g., AR-037):**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX -- Delta Spec\n\n## Changes\n\n### Additions\n<!-- New files, functions, features -->\n\n### Modifications\n<!-- Existing code that will change -->\n\n### Deletions\n<!-- Code to be removed -->\n```\n\n#### C. Root-level `delta-spec.md`\n\nThe root-level `/home/dsj/benchmark/.../delta-spec.md` is a **comprehensive, fully-populated delta spec** for AR-038 (Go unit tests for workloadmanager). It is 826 lines long and contains 12 requirement groups (R-1 through R-12) with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios.\n\n---\n\n### 3. OpenSpec Format Patterns\n\nThe project follows a **four-document workflow** for each change request (AR = AgentCube Request):\n\n| Document | Location | Purpose |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| `proposal.md` | `changes/AR-XXX/proposal.md` | High-level purpose, scope, impact analysis, alternatives, implementation plan, acceptance criteria |\n| `design.md` | `changes/AR-XXX/design.md` or root-level | Technical architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy |\n| `delta-spec.md` | `changes/AR-XXX/delta-spec.md` or root-level | Detailed behavioral requirements in GIVEN/WHEN/THEN format |\n| `tasks.md` | `changes/AR-XXX/tasks.md` | Implementation task breakdown with dependency graph |\n\n**Proposal.md structure:**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX -- <Title>\n**Module:** <module>\n**Language:** <language>\n**Size:** <S/M/L>\n\n## Purpose\n## Scope (In Scope / Out of Scope)\n## Impact Analysis (Dependencies, Affected Components, Risk Assessment)\n## Alternatives Considered\n## Implementation Plan (Phases with checkboxes)\n## Acceptance Criteria (checkboxes)\n## Status (checkboxes)\n```\n\n**Design.md structure:**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX: <Title> -- Design\n\n## 1. Architecture (Purpose, Scope, System Context diagram, Design Principles, Package Structure, Dependencies)\n## 2. Data Structures (Mock objects, fixtures, class signatures)\n## 3. API Contracts (tables of inputs/outputs/behaviors)\n## 4. Error Handling (classification, exception hierarchy)\n## 5. Testing Strategy (categories, test plans, mocking strategy, execution commands, coverage targets, risks)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Current State of docs/ Directory\n\nThe `docs/` directory is a **Docusaurus 3.x documentation site**:\n\n```\ndocs/\n├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Site config (TypeScript)\n├── sidebars.ts                   # Sidebar navigation\n├── package.json                  # Node.js dependencies\n├── babel.config.js\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── design.md                     # AR-042: Docusaurus setup design (795 lines)\n├── src/\n│   ├── components/\n│   │   ├── ApiEndpoint/          # MDX component for API docs\n│   │   └── K8sResource/          # MDX component for CRD docs\n│   ├── pages/\n│   │   ├── index.tsx             # Landing page\n│   │   └── markdown-page.md\n│   ├── css/custom.css\n│   └── theme/                    # Swizzled theme components\n├── docs/\n│   ├── intro.md                  # Project introduction\n│   ├── getting-started/\n│   │   ├── installation.md\n│   │   ├── quick-start.md\n│   │   └── configuration.md\n│   ├── architecture/\n│   │   ├── overview.md           # System architecture diagram + components\n│   │   ├── components.md\n│   │   ├── session-routing.md\n│   │   └── sandbox-lifecycle.md\n│   └── user-guide/\n│       ├── code-interpreter.md\n│       ├── agent-runtime.md\n│       └── cli.md\n└── static/\n```\n\n**Current documentation status:**\n- **Getting Started**: 3 docs (installation, quick-start, configuration)\n- **Architecture**: 4 docs (overview, components, session-routing, sandbox-lifecycle)\n- **User Guide**: 3 docs (code-interpreter, agent-runtime, cli)\n- **API Reference**: Directory exists in sidebar but files are **not yet created** (target of AR-043)\n- **Integrations**, **Operations**, **Contributing**: Defined in sidebar but **not yet populated**\n- **i18n/Chinese translations**: Framework ready, content not yet translated\n- **Versioned docs**: Framework ready, no versions created yet\n\n---\n\n### 5. Relevant Patterns for Writing Specs in This Project\n\n**Spec writing conventions:**\n\n1. **Normative language**: Use SHALL (mandatory), SHOULD (recommended), MAY (optional) per RFC 2119\n2. **BDD scenarios**: Every requirement has GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios\n3. **Requirement grouping**: Use `R-N:` prefixes (R-1, R-2, etc.) for requirement groups\n4. **Scope declarations**: Each requirement group declares `**Scope:**` with file/function paths\n5. **Context header**: Delta specs start with Module, Language, Size, and Base specs references\n6. **File structure tables**: End specs with a table of new/modified files\n7. **Dependencies section**: List external packages and whether they already exist (已有)\n8. **Status checkboxes**: Track progress through Spec review -> Implementation -> Verification\n\n**Design document conventions:**\n\n1. **Numbered sections**: 1. Architecture, 2. Data Structures, 3. API Contracts, 4. Error Handling, 5. Testing Strategy\n2. **ASCII architecture diagrams**: Box-drawing character diagrams for system context\n3. **Tables for data**: Class signatures, API contracts, test plans all use markdown tables\n4. **Code blocks for interfaces**: Go/Python/TypeScript signatures in fenced code blocks\n5. **Coverage targets**: Explicit percentage targets per module\n6. **Risk tables**: Risk + Mitigation pairs\n\n**Project context conventions (from project.md):**\n\n- Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n- Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n- JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n- K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n- AR numbering: AR-001 through AR-043 (currently)\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28423ba8dffeBpK4Uf1InNkHHT","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775899526511,"end":1775899629020}}}}
