{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899648865,"sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","part":{"id":"prt_d7bde1fae001vWmt0BKElTCX4k","messageID":"msg_d7bde10af001694d6cl85GvX9S","sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_920e0242eb764d539ce9fcf3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/sidebars.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/sidebars.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: import type { SidebarsConfig } from '@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs';\n2: \n3: const sidebars: SidebarsConfig = {\n4:   tutorialSidebar: [\n5:     'intro',\n6:     {\n7:       type: 'category',\n8:       label: 'Getting Started',\n9:       link: { type: 'doc', id: 'getting-started/installation' },\n10:       items: [\n11:         'getting-started/installation',\n12:         'getting-started/quick-start',\n13:         'getting-started/configuration',\n14:       ],\n15:     },\n16:     {\n17:       type: 'category',\n18:       label: 'Architecture',\n19:       link: { type: 'doc', id: 'architecture/overview' },\n20:       items: [\n21:         'architecture/overview',\n22:         'architecture/components',\n23:         'architecture/session-routing',\n24:         'architecture/sandbox-lifecycle',\n25:       ],\n26:     },\n27:     {\n28:       type: 'category',\n29:       label: 'User Guide',\n30:       link: { type: 'doc', id: 'user-guide/code-interpreter' },\n31:       items: [\n32:         'user-guide/code-interpreter',\n33:         'user-guide/agent-runtime',\n34:         'user-guide/cli',\n35:         'user-guide/python-sdk',\n36:       ],\n37:     },\n38:     {\n39:       type: 'category',\n40:       label: 'API Reference',\n41:       link: { type: 'doc', id: 'api-reference/control-plane' },\n42:       items: [\n43:         'api-reference/control-plane',\n44:         'api-reference/data-plane',\n45:         'api-reference/crds',\n46:       ],\n47:     },\n48:     {\n49:       type: 'category',\n50:       label: 'Integrations',\n51:       link: { type: 'doc', id: 'integrations/dify-plugin' },\n52:       items: [\n53:         'integrations/dify-plugin',\n54:         'integrations/langchain',\n55:       ],\n56:     },\n57:     {\n58:       type: 'category',\n59:       label: 'Operations',\n60:       link: { type: 'doc', id: 'operations/deployment' },\n61:       items: [\n62:         'operations/deployment',\n63:         'operations/monitoring',\n64:         'operations/troubleshooting',\n65:         'operations/security',\n66:       ],\n67:     },\n68:     {\n69:       type: 'category',\n70:       label: 'Contributing',\n71:       link: { type: 'doc', id: 'contributing/development' },\n72:       items: [\n73:         'contributing/development',\n74:         'contributing/testing',\n75:         'contributing/release-process',\n76:       ],\n77:     },\n78:   ],\n79: };\n80: \n81: export default sidebars;\n\n(End of file - total 81 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"import type { SidebarsConfig } from '@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs';\n\nconst sidebars: SidebarsConfig = {\n  tutorialSidebar: [\n    'intro',\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Getting Started',\n      link: { type: 'doc', id: 'getting-started/installation' },\n      items: [\n        'getting-started/installation',\n        'getting-started/quick-start',\n        'getting-started/configuration',\n      ],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Architecture',\n      link: { type: 'doc', id: 'architecture/overview' },\n      items: [","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/sidebars.ts","time":{"start":1775899648858,"end":1775899648864}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899649982,"sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","part":{"id":"prt_d7bde23d8001vLtBvR07aMDXnF","messageID":"msg_d7bde10af001694d6cl85GvX9S","sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_59790bebd1bf414bbf03082d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775899649976,"end":1775899649981}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899651264,"sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","part":{"id":"prt_d7bde2849001UUII14bRH3VSMq","messageID":"msg_d7bde10af001694d6cl85GvX9S","sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ee84d7e7101941aaaa159321","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: sidebar_position: 1\n3: title: Architecture Overview\n4: description: High-level system architecture of AgentCube\n5: keywords: [architecture, system-design, components, overview]\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Architecture Overview\n9: \n10: AgentCube is built as a set of loosely coupled microservices running on Kubernetes, communicating through a shared session store and the Kubernetes API.\n11: \n12: ## System Architecture\n13: \n14: ```\n15: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n16: │                        Kubernetes Cluster                         │\n17: │                                                                    │\n18: │  ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n19: │  │   Client     │────▶│           Router (Deployment)        │    │\n20: │  │  / SDK / CLI │     │         Session-Aware Proxy          │    │\n21: │  └─────────────┘     └──────────────┬───────────────────────┘    │\n22: │                                     │                             │\n23: │                            ┌────────▼────────┐                   │\n24: │                            │  Redis / Valkey  │                   │\n25: │                            │  (Session Store) │                   │\n26: │                            └────────┬─────────┘                   │\n27: │                                     │                             │\n28: │                   ┌─────────────────▼──────────────────┐          │\n29: │                   │     WorkloadManager (Controller)    │          │\n30: │                   │   - Sandbox Lifecycle Management    │          │\n31: │                   │   - CRD Reconciliation              │          │\n32: │                   │   - Resource Provisioning           │          │\n33: │                   └─────────────────┬──────────────────┘          │\n34: │                                     │                             │\n35: │                   ┌─────────────────▼──────────────────┐          │\n36: │                   │         Kubernetes API              │          │\n37: │                   │   - CRDs, Pods, Secrets, etc.       │          │\n38: │                   └─────────────────┬──────────────────┘          │\n39: │                                     │                             │\n40: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────▼──────────────────────┐     │\n41: │  │              Sandbox Pods                                │     │\n42: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐      │     │\n43: │  │  │  Sandbox 1  │  │  Sandbox 2  │  │  Sandbox N  │      │     │\n44: │  │  │  (PicoD)    │  │  (PicoD)    │  │  (PicoD)    │      │     │\n45: │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘      │     │\n46: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n47: │                                                                    │\n48: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n49: │  │              Agentd (Idle Cleanup Controller)              │    │\n50: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n51: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ## Design Principles\n55: \n56: 1. **Kubernetes-Native**: Built on CRDs and controller-runtime, integrating with K8s ecosystem\n57: 2. **Session-Aware**: All routing decisions are based on session state stored in Redis/Valkey\n58: 3. **Isolation-First**: Each agent workload runs in its own isolated sandbox\n59: 4. **Event-Driven**: Components react to Kubernetes events and session state changes\n60: 5. **Horizontally Scalable**: Router and WorkloadManager can scale independently\n61: \n62: ## Component Summary\n63: \n64: | Component | Type | Responsibility |\n65: |-----------|------|----------------|\n66: | **Router** | Deployment | HTTP proxy, session routing, load balancing |\n67: | **WorkloadManager** | Controller | Sandbox lifecycle, CRD reconciliation |\n68: | **Session Store** | StatefulSet/External | Session state, routing table |\n69: | **PicoD** | Sidecar/Daemon | Code execution inside sandboxes |\n70: | **Agentd** | Controller | Idle sandbox cleanup, resource reclamation |\n71: \n72: ## Data Flow\n73: \n74: 1. Client sends request to Router with session identifier\n75: 2. Router looks up session in Redis/Valkey to find target sandbox\n76: 3. If session exists, Router forwards request to sandbox\n77: 4. If no session, Router creates new session and signals WorkloadManager\n78: 5. WorkloadManager provisions sandbox pod via Kubernetes API\n79: 6. Once sandbox is ready, Router forwards request and caches routing info\n80: \n81: ## Next Steps\n82: \n83: - Dive into individual [Components](./components.md)\n84: - Learn about [Session Routing](./session-routing.md)\n85: - Understand [Sandbox Lifecycle](./sandbox-lifecycle.md)\n\n(End of file - total 85 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nsidebar_position: 1\ntitle: Architecture Overview\ndescription: High-level system architecture of AgentCube\nkeywords: [architecture, system-design, components, overview]\n---\n\n# Architecture Overview\n\nAgentCube is built as a set of loosely coupled microservices running on Kubernetes, communicating through a shared session store and the Kubernetes API.\n\n## System Architecture\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Kubernetes Cluster                         │\n│                                                                    │\n│  ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │   Client     │────▶│           Router (Deployment)        │    │\n│  │  / SDK / CLI │     │         Session-Aware Proxy          │    │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md","time":{"start":1775899651256,"end":1775899651262}}}}
