{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899654712,"sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","part":{"id":"prt_d7bde362f001scX9PC60jYIwTl","messageID":"msg_d7bde2ced001QK0iS8Jsl0MEuY","sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e81abafdc57c4acf9fb3e7e9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/components.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/components.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: sidebar_position: 2\n3: title: Components\n4: description: Deep dive into AgentCube's core components\n5: keywords: [components, router, workload-manager, picod, agentd]\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Components\n9: \n10: This page provides a deep dive into each core component of AgentCube.\n11: \n12: ## Router\n13: \n14: The Router is a session-aware HTTP proxy that directs incoming requests to the correct sandbox instance.\n15: \n16: ### Responsibilities\n17: \n18: - Accept HTTP requests from clients (SDK, CLI, direct API)\n19: - Look up session information in Redis/Valkey\n20: - Route requests to the appropriate sandbox pod\n21: - Create new sessions when none exists\n22: - Load balance across multiple WorkloadManager instances\n23: \n24: ### Technical Details\n25: \n26: - Built with Go using the Gin HTTP framework\n27: - Listens on port 8080 by default\n28: - Maintains a local cache of session-to-pod mappings\n29: - Supports JWT authentication for API requests\n30: \n31: ### Key Endpoints\n32: \n33: | Endpoint | Method | Description |\n34: |----------|--------|-------------|\n35: | `/api/v1/execute` | POST | Execute code in a sandbox |\n36: | `/api/v1/sessions` | GET | List active sessions |\n37: | `/api/v1/health` | GET | Health check |\n38: \n39: ## WorkloadManager\n40: \n41: The WorkloadManager is a Kubernetes controller that manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources.\n42: \n43: ### Responsibilities\n44: \n45: - Watch for CRD changes (CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime, Sandbox)\n46: - Reconcile desired state with actual cluster state\n47: - Create and manage sandbox pods\n48: - Handle resource provisioning (secrets, configmaps, volumes)\n49: - Report status back to CRD instances\n50: \n51: ### Technical Details\n52: \n53: - Built with Go using controller-runtime\n54: - Watches multiple CRD types in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group\n55: - Uses leader election for high availability\n56: - Integrates with Redis/Valkey for session state updates\n57: \n58: ### Reconciliation Loop\n59: \n60: ```\n61: Watch CRD → Compare desired vs actual → Create/Update/Delete pods → Update CRD status\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ## PicoD\n65: \n66: PicoD is an optional daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to handle code execution requests.\n67: \n68: ### Responsibilities\n69: \n70: - Receive code execution requests from the Router\n71: - Sanitize and execute code in a controlled environment\n72: - Enforce resource limits (CPU, memory, time)\n73: - Return execution results (output, exit code, errors)\n74: \n75: ### Technical Details\n76: \n77: - Lightweight Go binary\n78: - Listens on a port within the sandbox pod\n79: - Supports multiple languages (Python, Go, etc.)\n80: - Uses OS-level isolation (cgroups, namespaces)\n81: \n82: ## Agentd\n83: \n84: Agentd is an idle cleanup controller that reclaims unused sandbox resources.\n85: \n86: ### Responsibilities\n87: \n88: - Monitor sandbox activity via session store\n89: - Identify idle sandboxes exceeding the configured timeout\n90: - Gracefully terminate idle sandboxes\n91: - Clean up associated Kubernetes resources\n92: \n93: ### Technical Details\n94: \n95: - Runs as a Kubernetes controller\n96: - Configurable idle timeout (default: 30 minutes)\n97: - Periodic check interval (default: 5 minutes)\n98: - Graceful shutdown with configurable drain period\n99: \n100: ## Session Store (Redis/Valkey)\n101: \n102: The session store is the central state management component.\n103: \n104: ### Responsibilities\n105: \n106: - Store session-to-pod mappings\n107: - Track session TTL and activity timestamps\n108: - Support pub/sub for cross-component communication\n109: - Provide atomic operations for session creation/deletion\n110: \n111: ### Data Model\n112: \n113: ```\n114: Key: session:{sessionId}\n115: Value: {\n116:   \"podName\": \"sandbox-abc123\",\n117:   \"podIP\": \"10.0.0.5\",\n118:   \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n119:   \"lastActiveAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:05:00Z\",\n120:   \"status\": \"active\"\n121: }\n122: ```\n123: \n124: ## Next Steps\n125: \n126: - Learn about [Session Routing](./session-routing.md)\n127: - Understand [Sandbox Lifecycle](./sandbox-lifecycle.md)\n\n(End of file - total 127 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nsidebar_position: 2\ntitle: Components\ndescription: Deep dive into AgentCube's core components\nkeywords: [components, router, workload-manager, picod, agentd]\n---\n\n# Components\n\nThis page provides a deep dive into each core component of AgentCube.\n\n## Router\n\nThe Router is a session-aware HTTP proxy that directs incoming requests to the correct sandbox instance.\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n- Accept HTTP requests from clients (SDK, CLI, direct API)\n- Look up session information in Redis/Valkey\n- Route requests to the appropriate sandbox pod","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/components.md","time":{"start":1775899654705,"end":1775899654710}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899869991,"sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","part":{"id":"prt_d7bde3aae001lAmWvbZqK6zwju","messageID":"msg_d7bde2ced001QK0iS8Jsl0MEuY","sessionID":"ses_28423e195ffe8TXj4LBUSb69pE","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_002030e4161a4fcdae6fb81c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Find API endpoints in codebase","prompt":"Search the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z to find:\n\n1. All HTTP API endpoints defined in Go code (look for Gin router routes, handler functions, route registration)\n   - Check: session-routing/, pkg/, cmd/ directories\n   - Find route definitions like r.GET, r.POST, router.Group, etc.\n   \n2. All CRD definitions (look for Kubernetes Custom Resource Definitions)\n   - Check: manifests/, pkg/apis/, client-go/ directories\n   \n3. All Python SDK API methods\n   - Check: sdk-python/, python-sdk/ directories\n   \n4. All CLI commands\n   - Check: cli-toolkit/, cmd/cli/ directories\n\nReturn a comprehensive list of:\n- REST API endpoints (method, path, handler, description)\n- CRD types (kind, group, version, purpose)\n- SDK methods (class, method, description)\n- CLI commands (command, subcommands, description)","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28421ae08ffeDW4kxA6rOix6dr (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a complete picture of the project. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project -- Complete API/Surface Inventory\n\n---\n\n### 1. REST API ENDPOINTS\n\n#### 1A. Workload Manager API (`cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`)\nBase server: listens on configurable port, Gin engine\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/health/live` | `handleLive` | Liveness probe -- returns `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n| `GET` | `/health/ready` | inline handler | Readiness probe -- returns `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | `createHandler.CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox` / `createHandler.CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox` | Create a new sandbox session (dispatches based on `kind` field: `\"AgentRuntime\"` or `\"CodeInterpreter\"`) |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID` | `deleteHandler.DeleteSandbox` | Delete a sandbox by session ID |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID` | `lifecycleManager.GetSandboxStatus` | Get status of a specific sandbox session |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | `lifecycleManager.ListSandboxes` | List all sandboxes (supports `?namespace=` and `?status=` query params) |\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID/extend` | `lifecycleManager.ExtendSandboxTTL` | Extend a sandbox's TTL (body: `{\"extensionDuration\": \"...\"}`) |\n\n#### 1B. Router API (`pkg/router/server.go`)\nBase server: listens on configurable port, supports HTTP/HTTPS with h2c, JWT auth middleware, concurrency limiting\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/health/live` | `handleHealthLive` | Liveness probe -- returns `{\"status\": \"alive\"}` |\n| `GET` | `/health/ready` | `s.handleHealthReady` | Readiness probe -- checks session manager availability |\n| `GET` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `s.handleAgentInvoke` | Proxy GET request to an AgentRuntime sandbox (reverse proxy, adds `x-agentcube-session-id` response header) |\n| `POST` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `s.handleAgentInvoke` | Proxy POST request to an AgentRuntime sandbox (reverse proxy, adds `x-agentcube-session-id` response header) |\n| `GET` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | `s.handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` | Proxy GET request to a CodeInterpreter sandbox (reverse proxy) |\n| `POST` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | `s.handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` | Proxy POST request to a CodeInterpreter sandbox (reverse proxy) |\n\nThe router acts as a **reverse proxy**: it resolves the sandbox entry point from the session store, then forwards the request to the sandbox's pod IP. It injects `X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For` headers, and for Sandbox/SandboxClaim kinds, adds a JWT `Authorization: Bearer` token.\n\n#### 1C. PicoD API (`pkg/picod/server.go`)\nBase server: internal sandbox-side daemon, JWT public-key auth middleware on `/api/*`\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/health` | `s.HealthCheckHandler` | Health check -- returns service name, version, uptime |\n| `POST` | `/api/execute` | `s.ExecuteHandler` | Execute a shell command in the sandbox (body: `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"30s\", \"working_dir\": \"...\", \"env\": {...}}`) |\n| `POST` | `/api/files` | `s.UploadFileHandler` | Upload a file (supports both multipart/form-data and JSON base64 upload) |\n| `GET` | `/api/files` | `s.ListFilesHandler` | List files in a directory (query param: `?path=...`) |\n| `GET` | `/api/files/*path` | `s.DownloadFileHandler` | Download/stream a specific file from the sandbox |\n\n---\n\n### 2. CRD DEFINITIONS (Kubernetes Custom Resource Definitions)\n\n#### 2A. AgentRuntime\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go`\n- **CRD YAML**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Kind** | `AgentRuntime` |\n| **Group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n| **Scope** | Namespaced |\n| **Plural** | `agentruntimes` |\n| **Purpose** | Defines the runtime configuration for agent sessions. Specifies pod template, target ports, session timeout, and max session duration. The workload manager watches these CRs and creates Sandbox CRs from them. |\n\n**Spec fields:**\n- `targetPort[]` -- list of `TargetPort` (name, port, protocol HTTP/HTTPS, pathPrefix)\n- `podTemplate` -- `SandboxTemplate` containing labels, annotations, and a full `corev1.PodSpec`\n- `sessionTimeout` -- session idle timeout duration\n- `maxSessionDuration` -- maximum session lifetime (default: 8h)\n\n**Status fields:**\n- `conditions[]` -- standard `metav1.Condition` array\n\n#### 2B. CodeInterpreter\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n- **CRD YAML**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Kind** | `CodeInterpreter` |\n| **Group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n| **Scope** | Namespaced |\n| **Plural** | `codeinterpreters` |\n| **Purpose** | Defines the configuration for code interpreter sessions. Similar to AgentRuntime but with code-interpreter-specific fields like warm pool size and auth mode. |\n\n**Spec fields:**\n- `ports[]` -- list of `TargetPort`\n- `template` -- `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` (labels, annotations, runtimeClassName, image, imagePullPolicy, imagePullSecrets, environment env vars, command, args, resources)\n- `sessionTimeout` -- session idle timeout\n- `maxSessionDuration` -- max session lifetime (default: 8h)\n- `warmPoolSize` -- pre-warmed sandbox pool size (int32)\n- `authMode` -- authentication mode: `\"picod\"` or `\"none\"` (default: `\"picod\"`)\n\n**Status fields:**\n- `conditions[]` -- standard `metav1.Condition` array\n- `ready` -- boolean readiness flag\n\n#### 2C. Sandbox\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/agents/v1alpha1/sandbox_types.go`\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Kind** | `Sandbox` |\n| **Group** | `agents.x-k8s.io` |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n| **Scope** | Namespaced |\n| **Purpose** | Represents an actual running sandbox instance. Created by the workload manager from AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter templates. Contains replicas, lifecycle (shutdownTime), ports, and podTemplate spec. |\n\n**Spec fields:**\n- `image` -- container image\n- `command` -- command to run\n\n**Status fields:**\n- `phase` -- current phase string\n\n#### 2D. SandboxClaim (referenced in code, GVR defined)\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go`\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Kind** | `SandboxClaim` |\n| **Group** | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n| **Scope** | Namespaced |\n| **Purpose** | Used when `warmPoolSize > 0` on a CodeInterpreter. Claims a pre-warmed sandbox from the pool instead of creating a new one. |\n\n---\n\n### 3. PYTHON SDK API METHODS\n\n#### 3A. `CodeInterpreterClient` (high-level client)\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n\n| Class | Method | Signature | Description |\n|-------|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `__init__` | `(name, namespace, ttl, workload_manager_url, router_url, auth_token, verbose, session_id)` | Creates/manages a code interpreter session via control plane + data plane |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `__enter__` / `__exit__` | Context manager | Auto-calls `stop()` on exit |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `stop()` | `() -> None` | Idempotent cleanup: closes data plane, deletes session, closes HTTP session |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `execute_command()` | `(command: str, timeout: float) -> str` | Execute a shell command in the sandbox |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `run_code()` | `(language: str, code: str, timeout: float) -> str` | Run code (currently supports Python only: writes to `/tmp/code_<ts>.py`, then executes) |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `write_file()` | `(content: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | Write content to a file in the sandbox (base64 encoded) |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `upload_file()` | `(local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | Upload a local file to the sandbox (multipart) |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `download_file()` | `(remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None` | Download a file from the sandbox (streamed) |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `list_files()` | `(path: str) -> Any` | List files in a sandbox directory |\n\n#### 3B. `AgentRuntimeClient` (high-level client)\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n\n| Class | Method | Signature | Description |\n|-------|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `__init__` | `(agent_name, namespace, router_url, verbose, session_id, timeout, connect_timeout)` | Bootstraps session and creates data plane client |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `__enter__` / `__exit__` | Context manager | Auto-calls `close()` on exit |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `invoke()` | `(payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: float) -> Any` | Invoke the agent runtime with a JSON payload, returns parsed JSON response |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `close()` | `() -> None` | Close the underlying HTTP session |\n\n#### 3C. `ControlPlaneClient` (low-level)\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n\n| Class | Method | Signature | Description |\n|-------|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `__init__` | `(workload_manager_url, auth_token, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates HTTP session with Bearer auth (supports in-cluster SA token) |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `create_session()` | `(name, namespace, metadata, ttl) -> str` | `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` -- creates a session, returns `sessionId` |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `delete_session()` | `(session_id: str) -> bool` | `DELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` -- 404 treated as success |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `close()` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n\n#### 3D. `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (low-level)\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n\n| Class | Method | Signature | Description |\n|-------|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `__init__` | `(session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name, base_url, timeout, connect_timeout, ...)` | Creates HTTP session with `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `execute_command()` | `(command: str|List[str], timeout: float) -> str` | `POST api/execute` -- executes command, raises `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `run_code()` | `(language: str, code: str, timeout: float) -> str` | Writes code to temp file then executes (Python only) |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `write_file()` | `(content: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | `POST api/files` -- base64-encoded file write |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `upload_file()` | `(local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | `POST api/files` -- multipart file upload |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `download_file()` | `(remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None` | `GET api/files/{path}` -- streamed download |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `list_files()` | `(path: str) -> Any` | `GET api/files?path=...` -- returns JSON file listing |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `close()` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n\n#### 3E. `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (low-level)\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n\n| Class | Method | Signature | Description |\n|-------|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `__init__` | `(router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout, connect_timeout, ...)` | Creates HTTP session, builds base URL to invocation endpoint |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `bootstrap_session_id()` | `() -> str` | `GET` invocation endpoint, reads `x-agentcube-session-id` from response header |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `invoke()` | `(session_id, payload: Dict, timeout: float) -> Response` | `POST` invocation endpoint with JSON body and session header |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `close()` | `() -> None` | Close HTTP session |\n\n---\n\n### 4. CLI COMMANDS\n\nThe CLI is built with **Typer** and is invoked as `agentcube` (or `kubectl-agentcube`).\n- **File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n\n| Command | Subcommands | Key Options | Description |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|-------------|\n| `agentcube` | (root) | `--version`, `--verbose/-v` | Entry point -- shows help or version |\n| `agentcube pack` | -- | `-f/--workspace`, `--agent-name`, `--language`, `--entrypoint`, `--port`, `--build-mode`, `--description`, `--output`, `--verbose` | Package an agent workspace: validates structure, generates metadata (`agent_metadata.yaml`) and Dockerfile, processes dependencies (Python requirements.txt or Java pom.xml) |\n| `agentcube build` | -- | `-f/--workspace`, `-p/--proxy`, `--cloud-provider`, `--output`, `--verbose` | Build a container image from a packaged workspace: increments semver, validates prerequisites, builds locally (Docker) or via cloud provider |\n| `agentcube publish` | -- | `-f/--workspace`, `--version`, `--image-url`, `--image-username`, `--image-password`, `--description`, `--region`, `--cloud-provider`, `--provider` (agentcube/k8s), `--node-port`, `--replicas`, `--namespace`, `--verbose` | Publish a packaged agent to Kubernetes: pushes image, deploys as AgentRuntime CR (`--provider agentcube`) or standard Deployment+Service (`--provider k8s`) |\n| `agentcube invoke` | -- | `-f/--workspace`, `--payload` (JSON), `--header` (repeatable), `--provider` (agentcube/k8s), `--verbose` | Invoke a deployed agent with a JSON payload via HTTP POST to the agent endpoint |\n| `agentcube status` | -- | `-f/--workspace`, `--provider` (agentcube/k8s), `--verbose` | Check the status of a deployed agent: reads metadata, queries CR or Deployment, displays status table |\n\n#### CLI Runtime Classes (internal implementation):\n\n| Class | File | Key Methods |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `PackRuntime` | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `pack()` -- validates workspace, generates Dockerfile (Python/Java), saves metadata |\n| `BuildRuntime` | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `build()` -- increments version, validates, builds local (Docker) or cloud |\n| `PublishRuntime` | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `publish()` -- pushes image, deploys to K8s as CR or Deployment |\n| `InvokeRuntime` | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `invoke()` -- sends HTTP POST to agent endpoint (async via httpx) |\n| `StatusRuntime` | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `get_status()` -- queries CR or Deployment status |\n\n#### CLI Service Classes:\n\n| Class | File | Purpose |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `AgentCubeProvider` | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | Interacts with AgentRuntime CRs on K8s |\n| `KubernetesProvider` | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | Interacts with standard K8s Deployments/Services |\n| `MetadataService` | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Loads/saves `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n| `DockerService` | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Docker operations (build, push, login) |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28421ae08ffeDW4kxA6rOix6dr","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Find API endpoints in codebase","time":{"start":1775899660788,"end":1775899869989}}}}
